    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-30T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-30T18:00:00-05:00" n="54"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/3080: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-30T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 30, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>245. American interests France. Your 55, January 5.<note n="12" xml:id="d54fn12"
                        >Not printed; it concerned inquiry by Swiss Legation, Vichy, with respect to
                        repatriation of non-official Americans from former unoccupied zone in
                        France.</note> The Department contemplates no special arrangements for
                    repatriation of non-official Americans in the former unoccupied zone of France.
                    However, should any Americans in the former unoccupied zone obtain with or
                    without Swiss assistance exit permits for their individual travel to a neutral
                    country en route to the United States, Department would be pleased to be
                    informed thereof and would wish to be informed of their names.</p>
                <p>Lists of persons applying for repatriation as well as of those refusing
                    repatriation are of course desired because of their bearing upon question of
                    financial assistance to such individuals.</p>
                <p>You may inform Swiss of substance of foregoing in confidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
